annotationA: Thioredoxin peroxidase 2, isoform A; Protein binding; peroxidase activity; antioxidant activity; thioredoxin peroxidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to oxidative stress; positive regulation of JAK-STAT cascade; oxidation-reduction process; cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; positive regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway; apoptotic signaling pathway; cellular response to cold; hydrogen peroxide catabolic process; defense response to bacterium
annotationB: Death-associated inhibitor of apoptosis 1; Anti-apoptotic protein which functions as a caspase regulator, using its E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase activity to smother caspase activity. Binds, ubiquitinates and inactivates initiator caspase Dronc, and effector caspases Drice and Dcp-1. Acts as a Nedd8-E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase for Drice. Suppresses apoptosis by targeting the apoptosome for ubiquitination and inactivation. Plays an important role in cell motility. Overexpression suppresses rpr and hid-dependent cell death in the eye.
